{%- comment -%}
  preorder-status — the one pre-order status line, shared by product cards,
  the PDP buy area and the cart line so the wording never diverges.

  Renders a mono line with a pulsing dot:  ● Siuvimas · numatoma gegužės pab.
  Composed from two product metafields (pinned definitions, see spec
  docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-21-netrukus-preorder-preview-design.md):
    preorder.stage     — current production stage (choice list, Lithuanian)
    preorder.expected  — free-text expected window (e.g. „gegužės pabaiga")

  Renders NOTHING unless the product carries the `netrukus` tag (the single
  pre-order switch) and at least one of the two fields is set.

  Params:
    product (product) required
    class   (string)  optional — extra class on the wrapper (e.g. 'card__status')
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if product.tags contains 'netrukus' -%}
  {%- assign po_stage = product.metafields.preorder.stage.value -%}
  {%- assign po_expected = product.metafields.preorder.expected.value -%}
  {%- if po_stage != blank or po_expected != blank -%}
  <span class="postatus{% if class %} {{ class }}{% endif %}">
    <span class="postatus__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <span class="postatus__t">
      {%- if po_stage != blank -%}{{ po_stage }}{%- endif -%}
      {%- if po_stage != blank and po_expected != blank %} · {% endif -%}
      {%- if po_expected != blank -%}{{ 'product.preorder.expected' | t: date: po_expected }}{%- endif -%}
    </span>
  </span>
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
